  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Meals at the Valtur are a highlight of the holiday experience, offering a diverse and satisfying selection every day.</p>
<p>Start your day with a wide array of options from the hot and cold breakfast buffet. If you prefer, you can also order freshly made hot dishes delivered to your table, all prepared with the highest quality local ingredients. Coffee lovers can enjoy freshly brewed drinks served at the table, and tea enthusiasts will appreciate the variety of loose tea options available.</p>
<p>After a day of skiing, head to the bar to indulge in a fantastic selection of après-ski snacks while enjoying daily live entertainment. As an Inghams guest, you'll have access to the Executive Lounge, where you can enjoy soft drinks, tea, and coffee throughout the day.</p>
<p>For dinner, the Valtur offers two options. You can either choose the buffet package and eat dinner at the Gargantua restaurant, featuring a range of foods including fresh pizza and pasta stations, as well as a natural and wellness corner that caters to vegetarian and vegan diets. Alternatively, you can opt to pay a little extra (included for guests in a Junior Suite or Suite) for a three-course meal at the a la carte restaurant, Gou. Please ensure you pick the correct half board package at time of booking. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
