  <description><![CDATA[<p>With panoramic views and easy access to the slopes, the Valtur Cervinia Cristallo Ski Resort showcases the best that Cervinia has to offer. </p>
<h2>Slope access</h2>
<p>There are multiple easy ways to access the slopes from the Valtur. If you are heading out to the Plan Maison gondola and cable car you can hop on board the hotel's free shuttle everyday from 8:30am to 5:30pm.</p>
<p>The hotel is located just a fifteen minute walk from the Cielo Alto chairlift which leads to some challenging red and black runs. Also for intermediate skiers there is a magic carpet located just 50 metres from the hotel's ski room with access to red slope 16 and then on to Plan Maison.</p>
<h2>Dine around </h2>
<p>The Valtur offers a unique dining experience where guests can choose to have dinner at either of the hotel's two restaurants. You can enjoy a buffet dinner at the Gargantua, or a three course meal at the a la carte restaurant, Gou. Guests must book locally where they would like to dine.</p>
<h2>Facilities</h2>
<p>The hotel has extensive facilities including a 1,500m<sup>2</sup> wellness area complete with indoor pool, jacuzzi, multiple saunas, Turkish bath, ice fountain, salt wall, and relaxation areas. Some wellness facilities are payable locally.</p>
<p>The hotel also features a theatre, live music, and a sun terrace with excellent views.</p>]]></description>
